<br>
This statement is false. Monks may generally have a higher ac than rangers because of their ac bonus and higher defense skill caps but <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> hitpoints. <br>
<br>
Rangers start off with more hps than monks at level 1. The trend continues, the only way a monk will have more hps is if he/she has better equipment, which is definately not all stages of the game. <br>
<br>
I have been MA countless times in exp groups and have done a fine job. I have also been picked as MA over a monk same or higher level than myself for obvious reasons. <br>
<br>
I can taunt the mob to maintain aggro, monks aggro management is sparatic when working with other melees and casters. They cannot hold a secure bead on the mob all the time because they have no way to taunt the mob other than attacking.  I am not saying they don't ever, but it is more logical to use a tank who can actually hold aggro to do the job. Yes I know I am not the best person for the job either, but in situations as above I was the better choice. <br>
<br>
No monk is going to peel a mob off a wizard who just over nuked, or a shaman who just slowed the mob, that poor bastard is probably going to die. I on the other hand, would snare, root, taunt and already have the mob back on me. <br>
<br>
I don't appreciate the general lack of knowledge and misinformation being spread around about rangers. I have taken a lot of heat in my 2 and 1/2 years playing because people think it's fun to bash rangers. I am tired of defending my class and trying to tell people what I can really do.<br>
<br>
It's all fun and games to you, who bash us rangers but to us it's personal.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarayalebon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araya LeBon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#E9D756>(8/4/02 5:18:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrbazaar.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25706.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *</span><hr size=1> At all stages of the game a monk is able to focus on hps and hps alone due to our natural AC bonus.   Rangers have to really strive to crack 900 AC by level 55, Monks are hitting 1100 without even trying.  All I have to do is point you to the Ranger's Glade and Monkly-Business.com.  Go check out the hp tallies on the magelo's at respective levels.   Rangers generally sacrifice hps for AC.  I'm a very average equipped 60 monk and I have 2800ish hps 1160ish AC.  A few relatively minor upgrades and I'll be sitting around 3100hps.  Rangers in Skyshrine armor with much nicer gear than I are generally sitting around 2600hps with 1050-1100 AC and are generally stuck there til NToV stuff.  To crack 1000 AC you guys have to wear Lodi shields, Axgoreth Belt, IGS, etc...this gear has few to no hps.  Yea you get a higher base hp number due to the base modifier(which is VERY small) than a monk but you sacrifice hps/sta for AC.   Eventually it starts to even out but the top monks in the game are still beating the top rangers in hp numbers.<br>
<br>
I'm fully aware of the gear available to both classes.  I played a ranger as my first character for a LONG time.  <br>
In no way shape or form am I bashing rangers here, check my posts on the monk boards....I was among the first to say "F*** off" to the safehouse rogues who were sneaking in waving about their anti AM3/EQ propaganda.  <br>
<br>
As for rangers vs monks as MA.  A ranger makes a great peeler...and can certainly own us in aggro everytime, but a monk's higher avoidance and block skill(and higher hp numbers, once again...sorry) still make us far more efficient tank from a healer's perspective.  Rangers are great damage dealers, and certainly can be good MAs as well, but they just dont have the tools that monks have at their disposal(mend, stonestance, natural regen for iksar) to be AS efficient.  And btw I never have a problem pulling a mob off a shaman who has just slowed it, and I don't group with wizards that overnuke.  :P<br>
